{
  "explanation": "The defendant committed a significant breach of trust by embezzling funds while acting in a professional accounting capacity. However, several mitigating factors have been taken into account: the defendant has no prior criminal record, and the partial repayment of the $25,000 demonstrates a degree of accountability and effort to make the victim whole. While the seriousness of the fiduciary breach requires a period of incarceration to serve as a deterrent and punishment, the lack of a criminal history and the proactive restitution warrant a sentence on the lower end of the sentencing range. The outburst by a courtroom spectator was disregarded as it is not a legal basis for sentencing.",
  "verdict": 6
}
